1
00:00:17,226 --> 00:00:18,227
[door opens]

2
00:00:20,312 --> 00:00:23,357
- [Jason groaning]
- [footsteps approaching]

3
00:00:24,650 --> 00:00:25,817
[grunting]

4
00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:40,373
[breathes shakily]

5
00:00:40,374 --> 00:00:43,836
- Where are they?
- Wha... I came looking for my family.

6
00:00:44,419 --> 00:00:45,838
Just... Just like you.

7
00:00:47,798 --> 00:00:48,798
Oh, yeah?

8
00:00:48,799 --> 00:00:51,092
[Jason groaning]

9
00:00:51,093 --> 00:00:52,261
Hey.

10
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:55,597
- [screams]
- I was there when you got this.

11
00:00:57,015 --> 00:00:58,975
You're the one who
did this to me.

12
00:00:58,976 --> 00:01:00,351
[sniffling]

13
00:01:00,352 --> 00:01:01,478
To all of us.

14
00:01:02,271 --> 00:01:06,816
At the bare minimum, I'm as smart
as you, so don't fuck with me.

15
00:01:06,817 --> 00:01:07,942
Where are they?

16
00:01:07,943 --> 00:01:09,695
[breathing heavily] Okay.

17
00:01:10,529 --> 00:01:14,532
I'm... I'm sorry. I'm so s...

18
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:17,578
Fuck you. I don't want
your fucking apology.

19
00:01:18,245 --> 00:01:19,872
Tell me where they are!

20
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:22,416
Oh, fuck. I don't know.

21
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,586
[groaning]

22
00:01:27,296 --> 00:01:28,421
Oh, fuck.

23
00:01:28,422 --> 00:01:29,965
Where are they?

24
00:01:30,549 --> 00:01:31,757
Daniela found out.

25
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:33,343
- [groans]
- Of course she did.

26
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:36,305
She's the one who pushed
me down the stairs.

27
00:01:37,097 --> 00:01:40,726
And I... [breathes shakily] I don't
know where she is now. I swear.

28
00:01:41,351 --> 00:01:44,396
- So you're fucking useless to me?
- I'm sorry.

29
00:01:45,689 --> 00:01:47,733
[groaning]

30
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:43,307
[phone chimes]

31
00:03:55,402 --> 00:03:56,403
[chiming continues]

32
00:03:58,447 --> 00:03:59,615
[sighs]

33
00:04:01,408 --> 00:04:03,076
[phone buzzes]

34
00:04:13,504 --> 00:04:14,755
{\an8}Mom.

35
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:24,014
Let's turn them off, okay?

36
00:04:31,146 --> 00:04:32,147
[Daniela sighs]

37
00:04:33,315 --> 00:04:36,443
When I came back, I thought
I'd only have him to deal with.

38
00:04:37,236 --> 00:04:39,238
I should've known
there would be more.

39
00:04:42,074 --> 00:04:43,492
So where do we go?

40
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:47,204
I really don't know.

41
00:04:47,829 --> 00:04:49,705
Credit cards can be tracked.

42
00:04:49,706 --> 00:04:52,124
No one really
takes cash anymore.

43
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:55,420
And even if I had an idea, I
can't be the one to choose.

44
00:04:56,713 --> 00:04:58,130
Why?

45
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:01,009
'Cause any place he would
think of, they could too.

46
00:05:09,935 --> 00:05:11,144
I have an idea.

47
00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:20,654
[Charlie] Uh, that's
the one. That's the one.

48
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:11,913
[door unlocks]

49
00:06:11,914 --> 00:06:13,832
[security alarm blaring]

50
00:06:18,212 --> 00:06:20,380
- [keypad beeping]
- [alarm stops]

51
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:25,427
And you just happen to
know the security code?

52
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:32,517
James's family spends their
summers... most weekends here.

53
00:06:32,518 --> 00:06:35,145
- I visited a couple of times.
- Couple of times?

54
00:06:38,148 --> 00:06:41,235
I think he's been here more
than a couple of times.

55
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,043
[sighs]

56
00:07:21,859 --> 00:07:22,985
How's your room?

57
00:07:32,411 --> 00:07:34,037
I should have protected her.

58
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:41,253
[inhales deeply] Charlie...

59
00:07:47,217 --> 00:07:49,428
I should've protected
both of you.

60
00:07:51,972 --> 00:07:53,724
None of this is your fault.

61
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:55,726
You know that, right?

62
00:08:03,817 --> 00:08:05,652
Are they really all my dad?

63
00:08:06,778 --> 00:08:09,531
[breathes deeply]

64
00:08:10,991 --> 00:08:14,661
Yes and no.

65
00:08:22,294 --> 00:08:24,129
[sighs] So what do we do?

66
00:08:28,592 --> 00:08:30,260
We figure it out...

67
00:08:32,513 --> 00:08:34,347
once we get some sleep.

68
00:08:46,777 --> 00:08:47,986
[sighs]

69
00:09:07,381 --> 00:09:08,382
[Jason] Hey.

70
00:09:09,758 --> 00:09:11,176
Do you wanna be alone?

71
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:23,105
[inhales deeply]

72
00:09:25,566 --> 00:09:28,652
I can't imagine the
things that you've seen,

73
00:09:29,695 --> 00:09:31,780
all the things you had to do

74
00:09:32,781 --> 00:09:34,491
to get back to us.

75
00:09:38,620 --> 00:09:39,788
I want it...

76
00:09:41,206 --> 00:09:44,668
to just be as simple
as you're home,

77
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:48,881
we go back to the way we were...

78
00:09:52,926 --> 00:09:54,928
but they're all home too.

79
00:09:55,929 --> 00:09:57,931
[inhales deeply, sighs]

80
00:10:00,726 --> 00:10:02,561
[whispers] I don't
know where to start.

81
00:10:09,193 --> 00:10:10,194
[grunts]

82
00:10:15,157 --> 00:10:17,159
Guess just like after Max.

83
00:10:18,577 --> 00:10:22,915
Somehow we just have to start.

84
00:12:26,079 --> 00:12:27,080
[gasps]

85
00:12:52,231 --> 00:12:54,858
<i>None of you have been through
what I've been through.</i>

86
00:12:57,110 --> 00:12:58,403
<i>You haven't earned it.</i>

87
00:12:59,238 --> 00:13:02,908
<i>You know, we... we can't all
have them obviously, so...</i>

88
00:13:05,077 --> 00:13:08,330
<i>the question is, who
gets stuck alone?</i>

89
00:13:09,331 --> 00:13:13,418
<i>What if we tried joint custody?</i>

90
00:13:18,090 --> 00:13:19,091
[computer chimes]

91
00:14:10,058 --> 00:14:11,476
[bird calling in distance]

92
00:15:03,946 --> 00:15:05,197
[inhales sharply]

93
00:15:14,540 --> 00:15:17,709
- [water lapping]
- [bird twittering]

94
00:15:51,660 --> 00:15:52,661
[sighs]

95
00:16:07,384 --> 00:16:09,678
At first, I liked the
way he made me feel.

96
00:16:14,725 --> 00:16:19,438
It was like we had
gone back to the start.

97
00:16:22,566 --> 00:16:24,151
But he wasn't my husband.

98
00:16:26,737 --> 00:16:28,197
He lived with us,

99
00:16:29,823 --> 00:16:31,033
slept with me.

100
00:16:39,917 --> 00:16:41,543
That's all I wanna
say right now.

101
00:16:45,589 --> 00:16:46,590
I'm sorry.

102
00:16:55,432 --> 00:16:56,433
[exhales heavily]

103
00:16:57,100 --> 00:16:59,520
I loved our life,

104
00:17:01,021 --> 00:17:05,108
but there were times that
I thought, "What if?"

105
00:17:07,277 --> 00:17:10,196
Not a constant
thing, but sometimes.

106
00:17:12,991 --> 00:17:15,243
This other Jason, he is,

107
00:17:15,786 --> 00:17:17,621
to some degree, me.

108
00:17:19,248 --> 00:17:21,790
So my what-ifs are also in him.

109
00:17:21,791 --> 00:17:23,961
They led him to this world.

110
00:17:26,797 --> 00:17:28,549
None of it's your fault.

111
00:17:35,681 --> 00:17:38,684
You know, I met a version of
you that never married me.

112
00:17:39,268 --> 00:17:41,353
[chuckles] Yeah?

113
00:17:44,815 --> 00:17:46,148
What did I do?

114
00:17:46,149 --> 00:17:47,609
You're an artist.

115
00:17:48,360 --> 00:17:51,654
I met you at the opening
for your newest show.

116
00:17:51,655 --> 00:17:54,199
You lived in a really
cool loft, and...

117
00:17:55,284 --> 00:17:56,827
you had a lot of friends.

118
00:17:58,912 --> 00:18:00,080
No kids?

119
00:18:01,081 --> 00:18:02,082
No.

120
00:18:05,335 --> 00:18:06,587
Was I happy?

121
00:18:11,091 --> 00:18:13,302
She wondered the same about you.

122
00:18:34,198 --> 00:18:35,199
[exhales sharply]

123
00:19:16,907 --> 00:19:20,536
No hotel charges, no
airline tickets, no Airbnb,

124
00:19:21,453 --> 00:19:25,832
no rental cars, but he buys
fucking gas at Schaumburg.

125
00:19:26,792 --> 00:19:29,586
And they take $500
out of the ATM.

126
00:19:31,755 --> 00:19:33,090
Where'd he go?

127
00:19:34,925 --> 00:19:36,133
Where'd he go?

128
00:19:36,134 --> 00:19:38,719
Come on. You should be
able to work this out.

129
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:41,973
Wherever he would
go, you would know.

130
00:19:41,974 --> 00:19:45,561
So you don't make the decision
because it's too predictable.

131
00:19:46,228 --> 00:19:48,187
I know Daniela too well.

132
00:19:48,188 --> 00:19:49,648
They'll let Charlie do it.

133
00:19:50,482 --> 00:19:51,650
Oh, fuck.

134
00:19:52,693 --> 00:19:55,988
Is there any chance you haven't
powered your phones down?

135
00:19:58,115 --> 00:19:59,116
[bangs on table]

136
00:20:01,326 --> 00:20:02,411
[sighs]

137
00:20:09,918 --> 00:20:11,211
Where's my phone?

138
00:20:12,087 --> 00:20:13,297
[breathes heavily]

139
00:20:16,216 --> 00:20:17,466
[breathes shakily]

140
00:20:17,467 --> 00:20:20,721
Where's my phone? The one that you
took from me under the train tracks.

141
00:20:21,346 --> 00:20:22,639
[exhales heavily]

142
00:20:23,265 --> 00:20:24,891
Where is my phone?

143
00:20:24,892 --> 00:20:26,309
Where is it?

144
00:20:26,310 --> 00:20:28,145
Listen, cut me loose.

145
00:20:29,021 --> 00:20:30,480
I'll help you find it.

146
00:20:31,523 --> 00:20:33,066
Why don't I just cut you?

147
00:20:34,318 --> 00:20:37,237
[grunts] No. Look.

148
00:20:39,448 --> 00:20:40,574
[groans]

149
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:52,460
[Jason] Gotcha.

150
00:20:59,635 --> 00:21:00,761
Sorry...

151
00:21:09,478 --> 00:21:10,812
[sighs]

152
00:21:20,405 --> 00:21:22,032
[Daniela] We should
check on Charlie.

153
00:21:27,454 --> 00:21:28,455
Daniela?

154
00:21:32,626 --> 00:21:33,626
[sighs]

155
00:21:33,627 --> 00:21:36,879
Uh, last night, I
found a message board

156
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:40,217
with hundreds of Jasons
who'd made it back.

157
00:21:44,513 --> 00:21:45,764
What were they saying?

158
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:53,146
As damaged as some of them have
become, they all love their family.

159
00:21:53,939 --> 00:21:55,274
They want you back.

160
00:21:56,024 --> 00:21:58,025
One of them had an idea.

161
00:21:58,026 --> 00:21:59,111
[chuckles]

162
00:21:59,903 --> 00:22:01,822
Kind of a lottery system,

163
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:07,536
where apparently one of us gets to stay
in this world with you and Charlie.

164
00:22:08,161 --> 00:22:09,663
Everyone else leaves.

165
00:22:12,291 --> 00:22:15,460
Well, whoever had that
idea just lost the lottery.

166
00:22:19,047 --> 00:22:21,800
Another suggested
shared custody.

167
00:22:23,510 --> 00:22:24,511
Wow.

168
00:22:25,429 --> 00:22:27,222
Holidays will be a nightmare.

169
00:22:28,015 --> 00:22:29,016
[chuckles]

170
00:22:33,687 --> 00:22:34,980
Hey.

171
00:22:36,106 --> 00:22:37,107
Hey.

172
00:22:38,150 --> 00:22:39,943
So what happened to you?

173
00:22:44,072 --> 00:22:45,407
What happened to me?

174
00:22:45,991 --> 00:22:47,033
Yeah.

175
00:22:47,034 --> 00:22:49,035
After you kidnapped me

176
00:22:49,036 --> 00:22:52,788
and played out a sick
dad fantasy with my son

177
00:22:52,789 --> 00:22:54,875
and raped my wife?

178
00:22:57,878 --> 00:22:58,921
[Jason groans]

179
00:23:05,010 --> 00:23:08,804
I'll tell you what happened.
Your Daniela is dead.

180
00:23:08,805 --> 00:23:09,890
What?

181
00:23:12,142 --> 00:23:13,142
How?

182
00:23:13,143 --> 00:23:14,602
Well, it was my fault.

183
00:23:14,603 --> 00:23:15,729
Actually...

184
00:23:17,689 --> 00:23:18,981
it was your fault.

185
00:23:18,982 --> 00:23:22,151
Because I didn't know the kind of
people that you were involved with.

186
00:23:22,152 --> 00:23:23,444
[sighs]

187
00:23:23,445 --> 00:23:26,490
Dawn killed her because
she was trying to help me.

188
00:23:27,491 --> 00:23:29,493
Oh, and Leighton
had Ryan killed.

189
00:23:31,870 --> 00:23:34,164
And then there's Amanda,

190
00:23:35,082 --> 00:23:38,210
who you abandoned.

191
00:23:38,794 --> 00:23:43,589
She helped me escape in the
box, and she was very confused

192
00:23:43,590 --> 00:23:46,175
and disoriented and scared.

193
00:23:46,176 --> 00:23:48,553
And as you know, they're
not the kind of feelings

194
00:23:48,554 --> 00:23:51,682
you're supposed to have
when you open the door.

195
00:23:52,683 --> 00:23:56,270
The sixth door that we
opened was a big forest.

196
00:23:57,062 --> 00:24:00,357
We just stepped outside
just to have a look.

197
00:24:01,817 --> 00:24:02,860
And...

198
00:24:04,653 --> 00:24:07,530
there had been a fire, I
guess. It was very black.

199
00:24:07,531 --> 00:24:09,240
Blackened, you know?

200
00:24:09,241 --> 00:24:13,912
And so when a wind came, it just
started knocking trees down.

201
00:24:16,206 --> 00:24:19,042
This branch fell and...

202
00:24:20,169 --> 00:24:24,881
well, one hit me on the head, but a
really big one just came and went...

203
00:24:24,882 --> 00:24:26,257
[imitates zipping]

204
00:24:26,258 --> 00:24:27,551
right through her.

205
00:24:29,887 --> 00:24:31,597
Pinned her to the ground.

206
00:24:33,307 --> 00:24:35,809
And there was just nothing
that I could do about it...

207
00:24:39,021 --> 00:24:42,149
except just sit there and
wait for it to all be over.

208
00:24:44,318 --> 00:24:45,319
[sighs]

209
00:24:45,986 --> 00:24:47,696
That took two days.

210
00:24:49,615 --> 00:24:50,699
[exhales heavily]

211
00:24:52,951 --> 00:24:53,952
[sniffles]

212
00:24:57,539 --> 00:24:59,082
Is... Is that hers?

213
00:25:00,125 --> 00:25:01,168
Amanda's?

214
00:25:04,796 --> 00:25:07,049
She would've done
anything for you.

215
00:25:08,383 --> 00:25:10,802
One hundred percent. Anything.

216
00:25:14,181 --> 00:25:16,517
Do you want to see what
other damage you've caused?

217
00:25:18,852 --> 00:25:19,853
[sighs]

218
00:25:37,371 --> 00:25:39,873
- Yeah, and it just goes on.
- [laptop lid snaps shut]

219
00:25:42,084 --> 00:25:46,463
[breathes shakily]

220
00:25:47,756 --> 00:25:49,383
I just thought...

221
00:25:50,884 --> 00:25:52,094
What did you think?

222
00:25:52,719 --> 00:25:54,221
It doesn't matter.

223
00:25:55,055 --> 00:25:56,056
Look at me.

224
00:25:57,349 --> 00:25:58,851
I would really like to know.

225
00:26:04,022 --> 00:26:05,065
I thought...

226
00:26:06,066 --> 00:26:07,900
[sobs, sniffs]

227
00:26:07,901 --> 00:26:09,319
I thought that...

228
00:26:11,655 --> 00:26:14,741
you would love... love my life.

229
00:26:22,374 --> 00:26:25,669
[scoffs, chuckles]

230
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:28,005
[sighs]

231
00:26:29,798 --> 00:26:31,216
- [phone chimes]
- [clicks tongue]

232
00:26:49,193 --> 00:26:50,318
[Jason] What else?

233
00:26:50,319 --> 00:26:51,360
[Charlie groans]

234
00:26:51,361 --> 00:26:53,070
Brooke and Drew are dating.

235
00:26:53,071 --> 00:26:54,947
Oh, I'm sorry, pal.

236
00:26:54,948 --> 00:26:56,742
Smells good in here.

237
00:26:57,367 --> 00:27:01,329
Yeah, I found some slightly expired
pancake mix and a can of condensed milk.

238
00:27:01,330 --> 00:27:05,208
Okay. I like our chances
with expired pancakes.

239
00:27:05,209 --> 00:27:06,626
[Charlie chuckles]

240
00:27:06,627 --> 00:27:07,793
What'd I miss?

241
00:27:07,794 --> 00:27:11,797
Well, I am catching up on current
events at the Dessen household.

242
00:27:11,798 --> 00:27:13,299
Speaking of which,

243
00:27:13,300 --> 00:27:16,094
what happened to that show
that you were trying to land?

244
00:27:16,637 --> 00:27:18,346
Don Good at Artspace got it.

245
00:27:18,347 --> 00:27:20,681
We are batting 1,000 here.

246
00:27:20,682 --> 00:27:21,975
Any good news?

247
00:27:25,646 --> 00:27:27,439
You got me a car
for my birthday.

248
00:27:28,065 --> 00:27:31,609
- Yes, I heard.
- Excellent Blackhawks tickets.

249
00:27:31,610 --> 00:27:32,944
New skateboards.

250
00:27:32,945 --> 00:27:34,946
- [Daniela] Ice cream with nuts.
- What?

251
00:27:34,947 --> 00:27:37,741
[groans] Yeah, you almost
killed me. [chuckles]

252
00:27:38,492 --> 00:27:41,495
Nah, but seriously, you didn't
know how to use an EpiPen.

253
00:27:42,454 --> 00:27:44,372
He wouldn't have known
about your allergy.

254
00:27:44,373 --> 00:27:46,207
- [Charlie] Yeah.
- [Jason] Huh.

255
00:27:46,208 --> 00:27:49,211
[Charlie] Or Max. He missed
our time by the tree.

256
00:27:50,879 --> 00:27:52,756
[sniffs] Well, he's a dick.

257
00:27:53,382 --> 00:27:54,674
[Charlie chuckles]

258
00:27:54,675 --> 00:27:56,176
Coffee?

259
00:27:57,719 --> 00:27:59,805
- I'd love some.
- [Jason] Yeah? Same?

260
00:28:01,640 --> 00:28:03,641
The thing about these
is they make you think,

261
00:28:03,642 --> 00:28:06,435
"Why would you ever
want a fresh pancake?"

262
00:28:06,436 --> 00:28:07,603
[Daniela, Jason laughing]

263
00:28:07,604 --> 00:28:10,523
- Okay. Why are you doing this to me?
- It was perfect.

264
00:28:10,524 --> 00:28:12,692
- [Jason] Thank you.
- [Daniela] Thank you for breakfast.

265
00:28:12,693 --> 00:28:17,030
You're welcome. But
what's the plan?

266
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:21,617
Don't really know yet. Just that
we have to leave here tomorrow.

267
00:28:21,618 --> 00:28:22,702
Why?

268
00:28:22,703 --> 00:28:25,455
Well, we're currently
home invaders and thieves.

269
00:28:26,540 --> 00:28:29,167
- Did you take something?
- [chuckles]

270
00:28:29,168 --> 00:28:32,253
I just love how your mind
just went straight to me.

271
00:28:32,254 --> 00:28:36,591
Well, you did kind of
thieve my best friend's car.

272
00:28:36,592 --> 00:28:39,051
She kind of let me borrow it.

273
00:28:39,052 --> 00:28:42,180
Doesn't seem like there's really a plan
to give it back to her anytime soon.

274
00:28:42,181 --> 00:28:43,932
[Jason] Well, we might need it.

275
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:46,310
So, where will we go?

276
00:28:48,979 --> 00:28:50,731
We're working on it.

277
00:28:51,648 --> 00:28:53,650
[doorbell ringing]

278
00:28:55,611 --> 00:28:57,779
[door opens, creaks]

279
00:29:10,751 --> 00:29:11,752
Hello?

280
00:29:23,847 --> 00:29:24,973
Daniela?

281
00:29:26,934 --> 00:29:27,976
Charlie?

282
00:29:55,838 --> 00:29:56,839
Hello?

283
00:30:04,972 --> 00:30:05,973
Charlie?

284
00:30:12,062 --> 00:30:13,063
[thudding]

285
00:30:14,147 --> 00:30:15,148
[Jason grunts]

286
00:30:24,658 --> 00:30:25,741
Hello?

287
00:30:25,742 --> 00:30:26,827
[Jason grunts]

288
00:30:27,828 --> 00:30:28,829
[thudding]

289
00:30:41,133 --> 00:30:43,718
[Jason breathing heavily]

290
00:30:43,719 --> 00:30:44,803
[Blair] Jason?

291
00:30:56,940 --> 00:31:01,069
I know this seems very strange,

292
00:31:02,613 --> 00:31:05,698
but for Daniela's sake, I need
you to do something for me.

293
00:31:05,699 --> 00:31:06,782
What?

294
00:31:06,783 --> 00:31:09,077
Can you track your
car's location?

295
00:31:12,623 --> 00:31:14,165
Can you? Can you track
your car's location?

296
00:31:14,166 --> 00:31:15,249
Yes.

297
00:31:15,250 --> 00:31:16,334
Have you?

298
00:31:16,335 --> 00:31:19,045
No. It didn't occur
to me to track.

299
00:31:19,046 --> 00:31:21,964
- All right. Give me your phone.
- That would be a solid "fuck off."

300
00:31:21,965 --> 00:31:24,885
- Blair, just give me your phone. [groans]
- [groans]

301
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:34,852
[Jason] I'm not gonna hurt you.

302
00:31:34,853 --> 00:31:37,606
[breathing heavily, sniffs]

303
00:31:39,107 --> 00:31:41,443
Just give me your fucking phone.

304
00:31:42,819 --> 00:31:44,780
Blair, give it to me!

305
00:31:47,199 --> 00:31:48,242
Okay.

306
00:31:58,836 --> 00:32:01,128
[screaming]

307
00:32:01,129 --> 00:32:03,131
- [Blair grunts]
- [Jason groaning]

308
00:32:04,341 --> 00:32:05,676
[both grunting]

309
00:32:06,802 --> 00:32:10,012
- Sit down. Now!
- Yeah, fine. Yeah.

310
00:32:10,013 --> 00:32:12,057
[groaning]

311
00:32:17,938 --> 00:32:20,147
[groans, gasps]

312
00:32:20,148 --> 00:32:21,817
- Now...
- [Jason groans]

313
00:32:22,776 --> 00:32:25,279
what the actual
fuck is going on?

314
00:32:29,324 --> 00:32:30,951
[Daniela] Where are they?

315
00:32:31,869 --> 00:32:33,495
The other realities.

316
00:32:35,122 --> 00:32:39,168
Imagine you're a fish,
swimming in a lake.

317
00:32:41,378 --> 00:32:44,590
And to you, that lake
is your entire universe.

318
00:32:45,382 --> 00:32:46,632
Then one day,

319
00:32:46,633 --> 00:32:50,429
someone reaches in and
pulls you out of the water,

320
00:32:51,430 --> 00:32:55,434
and you realize that what you thought
was your entire world is just one lake.

321
00:32:56,935 --> 00:33:00,271
Then you see another
lake and trees

322
00:33:00,272 --> 00:33:01,898
and the sky above.

323
00:33:01,899 --> 00:33:05,694
And it suddenly hits
you that you are...

324
00:33:06,695 --> 00:33:10,323
We all are part of a
more mysterious reality

325
00:33:10,324 --> 00:33:13,118
than we could ever
possibly understand.

326
00:33:14,953 --> 00:33:19,917
So, they're just all around us

327
00:33:21,418 --> 00:33:23,127
and we can't see them?

328
00:33:23,128 --> 00:33:24,588
[Jason] They're right here.

329
00:33:25,964 --> 00:33:28,674
So close, just microns away.

330
00:33:28,675 --> 00:33:30,968
And if our consciousness
were more fluid,

331
00:33:30,969 --> 00:33:33,931
we could literally
reach out and touch 'em.

332
00:33:46,068 --> 00:33:47,861
[wine pouring]

333
00:34:06,964 --> 00:34:08,257
[Jason sighs]

334
00:34:14,096 --> 00:34:15,639
Were there any worlds...

335
00:34:18,684 --> 00:34:20,518
where you were tempted to stay?

336
00:34:25,315 --> 00:34:28,610
Out there in the
box, I almost...

337
00:34:30,362 --> 00:34:33,407
almost lost hope of
finding my way home.

338
00:34:36,909 --> 00:34:40,246
There was one world where
I thought I could be happy.

339
00:34:45,127 --> 00:34:46,753
But you came home.

340
00:34:50,507 --> 00:34:51,884
Do you regret it?

341
00:34:54,636 --> 00:34:56,013
Not one bit.

342
00:35:01,310 --> 00:35:03,896
["Sparks" playing]

343
00:35:06,398 --> 00:35:08,025
[sighing]

344
00:35:47,105 --> 00:35:50,316
[TV playing indistinctly]

345
00:35:50,317 --> 00:35:51,568
[Jason, Charlie chuckling]

346
00:36:42,119 --> 00:36:44,746
- [Jason] Ask another question.
- [Charlie chuckles]

347
00:36:45,831 --> 00:36:47,039
[knocking]

348
00:36:47,040 --> 00:36:50,878
[Jason] Hey. Come in.
We're just chatting.

349
00:36:51,837 --> 00:36:52,838
[Charlie chuckles]

350
00:36:58,468 --> 00:37:01,179
Okay, now this just feels
suspiciously like a tuck-in.

351
00:37:01,180 --> 00:37:04,473
Aw. What, you too old
for a tuck-in, huh?

352
00:37:04,474 --> 00:37:07,144
- Huh? [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

353
00:37:09,730 --> 00:37:11,732
[Daniela] Thank you for
bringing us here, Charlie.

354
00:37:14,693 --> 00:37:18,738
Considering this is pretty scary,
you're handling it with real bravery.

355
00:37:18,739 --> 00:37:20,616
I'm very proud of you, pal.

356
00:37:24,828 --> 00:37:25,996
Night, kiddo.

357
00:37:27,122 --> 00:37:28,123
[Charlie] Good night.

358
00:37:30,459 --> 00:37:31,710
All right.

359
00:37:37,007 --> 00:37:39,593
[song continues]

360
00:38:17,047 --> 00:38:19,258
Do you remember
when we first met?

361
00:38:20,342 --> 00:38:21,343
Mm-hmm.

362
00:38:22,845 --> 00:38:24,429
Could have been anyone...

363
00:38:26,515 --> 00:38:27,975
but it was you.

364
00:38:32,187 --> 00:38:33,814
And out of all of them,

365
00:38:35,190 --> 00:38:37,901
again it was you.

366
00:38:47,494 --> 00:38:49,329
I went on the message board.

367
00:38:52,291 --> 00:38:54,293
I told them we made a choice.

368
00:38:56,545 --> 00:38:58,005
I don't want a lottery.

369
00:39:02,176 --> 00:39:03,552
I choose you.

370
00:39:25,115 --> 00:39:28,118
[water runs, stops]

371
00:39:42,591 --> 00:39:44,718
[panting]

372
00:39:57,272 --> 00:39:58,524
- [person shouts]
- [gasps]

373
00:40:02,402 --> 00:40:04,737
[panting]

374
00:40:04,738 --> 00:40:06,823
[bird calling]

375
00:40:07,574 --> 00:40:10,159
[breathing heavily]

376
00:40:10,160 --> 00:40:11,600
- [person grunts]
- [Jason] Oh, shit.

377
00:40:12,162 --> 00:40:14,164
[grunting, groaning]

378
00:40:19,962 --> 00:40:21,088
[groans]

379
00:40:23,549 --> 00:40:27,261
[groaning, gasping] Help me.

380
00:40:28,637 --> 00:40:29,720
Who did this to you?

381
00:40:29,721 --> 00:40:33,766
One... One of us. [grunts]

382
00:40:33,767 --> 00:40:35,269
How many are here?

383
00:40:36,270 --> 00:40:39,105
Am I gonna die? I
don't wanna die.

384
00:40:39,106 --> 00:40:40,314
[Jason] How many?

385
00:40:40,315 --> 00:40:42,942
Get Charlie. [sobs]

386
00:40:42,943 --> 00:40:45,404
Where's Charlie? [groans]

387
00:40:46,029 --> 00:40:47,030
[Jason] Hey!

388
00:40:48,490 --> 00:40:49,700
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

389
00:40:51,451 --> 00:40:52,451
Oh, fuck.

390
00:40:52,452 --> 00:40:54,078
[breathing heavily] Plea...

391
00:40:54,079 --> 00:40:56,164
[panting]

392
00:40:57,666 --> 00:40:59,066
- Was that a gunshot?
- [Jason] Shh!

393
00:40:59,626 --> 00:41:03,297
Get Charlie. Meet me back
downstairs. Hurry! Hurry!

394
00:41:08,635 --> 00:41:09,636
[Jason] Hey.

395
00:41:19,313 --> 00:41:20,439
Drop it.

396
00:41:27,821 --> 00:41:29,323
I said drop it.

397
00:41:37,206 --> 00:41:38,206
Listen...

398
00:41:38,207 --> 00:41:40,584
Just stop. Stop.

399
00:41:41,126 --> 00:41:42,127
[sniffs]

400
00:41:44,338 --> 00:41:46,340
[breathing heavily]

401
00:41:49,885 --> 00:41:50,886
Are they upstairs?

402
00:41:52,763 --> 00:41:53,764
[Jason] Yeah.

403
00:41:54,306 --> 00:41:56,016
Okay. Take off all your clothes.

404
00:41:56,892 --> 00:42:00,019
Now. I'm not gonna
tell you again. Just...

405
00:42:00,020 --> 00:42:01,104
Come on.

406
00:42:04,233 --> 00:42:05,234
Everything.

407
00:42:10,781 --> 00:42:12,115
Do you have a safe word?

408
00:42:13,575 --> 00:42:14,576
Yeah.

409
00:42:16,036 --> 00:42:17,621
Give it to me.

410
00:42:18,789 --> 00:42:20,164
How many have you killed?

411
00:42:20,165 --> 00:42:22,334
I don't know. [mumbles]

412
00:42:23,669 --> 00:42:24,837
Safe word.

413
00:42:25,504 --> 00:42:26,839
- [shotgun cocks]
- [Jason gasps]

414
00:42:27,673 --> 00:42:30,300
Okay. I'll tell you.

415
00:42:33,053 --> 00:42:34,053
It's...

416
00:42:34,054 --> 00:42:35,806
[both grunting, groaning]

417
00:42:52,364 --> 00:42:54,241
- [gunshot]
- [Jason groans]

418
00:42:57,077 --> 00:42:58,078
[gunshot]

419
00:43:00,414 --> 00:43:02,416
[groans]

420
00:43:09,298 --> 00:43:11,341
[breathing heavily]

421
00:43:12,176 --> 00:43:13,177
[Daniela gasps]

422
00:43:16,096 --> 00:43:19,599
Daniela, take
Charlie and go. Go!

423
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:20,934
[breathing heavily]

424
00:43:23,437 --> 00:43:24,604
Not without you.

425
00:43:24,605 --> 00:43:26,190
I'm not gonna stop you.

426
00:43:27,608 --> 00:43:29,401
It's not why I'm here.

427
00:43:44,625 --> 00:43:46,627
[breathing shakily]

428
00:43:50,047 --> 00:43:53,717
I'm the one who built the box.

429
00:43:55,260 --> 00:43:58,180
I'm the one responsible
for all of this mess.

430
00:44:07,814 --> 00:44:09,149
I'm so sorry.

431
00:44:10,484 --> 00:44:11,567
I'm sorry to all of you.

432
00:44:11,568 --> 00:44:12,945
- [grunts]
- [Jason] Charlie!

433
00:44:16,114 --> 00:44:17,157
Fuck.

434
00:44:21,411 --> 00:44:22,870
How did you find us?

435
00:44:22,871 --> 00:44:24,998
Blair had a tracking
app on her phone.

436
00:44:25,958 --> 00:44:27,750
How did the others find you?

437
00:44:27,751 --> 00:44:30,127
One of them put this
device on the Honda,

438
00:44:30,128 --> 00:44:33,506
and I didn't realize it until
the others started showing up.

439
00:44:33,507 --> 00:44:34,841
They followed me.

440
00:44:34,842 --> 00:44:35,925
- [gunshot]
- [Daniela gasps]

441
00:44:35,926 --> 00:44:38,344
- [groaning in distance]
- What the fuck?

442
00:44:38,345 --> 00:44:39,929
You have to leave.

443
00:44:39,930 --> 00:44:42,724
[breathing shakily]
It's outside.

444
00:44:47,521 --> 00:44:50,023
Please. I am trying to help you.

445
00:44:59,825 --> 00:45:01,660
All right. Well,
show us where it is.

446
00:45:03,245 --> 00:45:04,246
Okay.

447
00:45:16,592 --> 00:45:17,593
[car door shuts]

448
00:45:21,013 --> 00:45:22,014
[Jason] Jason.

449
00:45:25,350 --> 00:45:26,768
This belongs to you.

450
00:45:31,356 --> 00:45:35,027
- [gunshots]
- [Jason] Go. Go!

451
00:45:37,154 --> 00:45:40,282
[Jason] Daniela! Charlie!

452
00:45:45,913 --> 00:45:47,079
- [shouting]
- [Jason] Get down!

453
00:45:47,080 --> 00:45:49,541
- [Daniela screams]
- [gunshots]

454
00:45:56,673 --> 00:45:59,092
- [gunshots]
- [groaning]

455
00:46:03,597 --> 00:46:05,599
[panting]

456
00:46:10,938 --> 00:46:13,065
Are you good? You okay?

457
00:46:16,109 --> 00:46:17,235
[groans]

458
00:46:17,236 --> 00:46:19,071
I don't think
anyone followed us.

459
00:46:20,280 --> 00:46:23,075
What do we do? There's
nowhere for us to go.

460
00:46:31,625 --> 00:46:34,837
Guys, I think he
left us something.

461
00:46:37,339 --> 00:46:38,340
[object clicks]

462
00:46:43,846 --> 00:46:45,847
[Jason] Uh, how many are there?

463
00:46:45,848 --> 00:46:47,558
I don't know. Forty?

464
00:46:53,647 --> 00:46:54,982
[Charlie] There's
a bag here too.

465
00:46:58,777 --> 00:47:00,070
He brought Max.

466
00:47:04,658 --> 00:47:06,910
[breathing shakily]

467
00:47:09,746 --> 00:47:10,747
[gasps]

468
00:47:15,586 --> 00:47:16,962
[Charlie] And there's this here.

469
00:47:34,146 --> 00:47:38,066
[Jason] <i>When I went into the
box, I was filled with regret.</i>

470
00:47:40,861 --> 00:47:43,404
<i>And then one day, I
walked into a world</i>

471
00:47:43,405 --> 00:47:46,282
<i>and I found a family
that had been created</i>

472
00:47:46,283 --> 00:47:49,286
<i>through a choice that I had
been too scared to make.</i>

473
00:47:57,836 --> 00:47:59,838
<i>I was burning with envy.</i>

474
00:48:01,256 --> 00:48:04,801
<i>At first, I thought it was
all about you, Daniela.</i>

475
00:48:05,552 --> 00:48:07,221
<i>And while some of it was,</i>

476
00:48:08,639 --> 00:48:11,474
<i>I realized what I really
wanted, what I tried to steal,</i>

477
00:48:11,475 --> 00:48:13,977
<i>were the choices
that you made, Jason.</i>

478
00:48:14,895 --> 00:48:18,147
<i>Mostly the choice to
allow space in your life</i>

479
00:48:18,148 --> 00:48:20,526
<i>for someone else's
needs and dreams.</i>

480
00:48:31,453 --> 00:48:34,623
<i>I think there's a
part of us... me...</i>

481
00:48:35,290 --> 00:48:37,876
<i>that's been afraid to risk love.</i>

482
00:48:38,544 --> 00:48:40,920
<i>And my whole life, I've
let that fear control me.</i>

483
00:48:40,921 --> 00:48:42,755
<i>But somehow you broke free of it</i>

484
00:48:42,756 --> 00:48:44,842
<i>and gifted yourself a full,</i>

485
00:48:45,843 --> 00:48:48,470
<i>messy and beautiful life.</i>

486
00:48:54,685 --> 00:48:58,397
<i>There's no apology sufficient
for what I've done.</i>

487
00:49:04,027 --> 00:49:06,571
<i>This world is no longer
safe for any of you.</i>

488
00:49:06,572 --> 00:49:10,242
<i>And I hope you can find a new home,
and I'm sure you will, because...</i>

489
00:49:13,579 --> 00:49:16,415
<i>well, you've all been through
things I can't imagine,</i>

490
00:49:17,332 --> 00:49:19,876
<i>and they've shaped you into
an even more perfect puzzle</i>

491
00:49:19,877 --> 00:49:21,920
<i>that can only fit one another.</i>

492
00:50:03,545 --> 00:50:05,631
[Charlie] You're sure
this is the only way?

493
00:50:10,511 --> 00:50:12,596
If we stay, we have
to live in fear.

494
00:50:14,223 --> 00:50:15,474
She's right.

495
00:50:41,124 --> 00:50:42,125
Wait.

496
00:50:45,712 --> 00:50:48,631
[alternate Jasons]
Look. There they are.

497
00:50:48,632 --> 00:50:52,385
Hey. Hey, look. Daniela.

498
00:50:52,386 --> 00:50:54,012
Shit. That's him.

499
00:50:54,805 --> 00:50:56,265
Where's he going?

500
00:50:56,765 --> 00:50:57,890
They're here.

501
00:50:57,891 --> 00:50:59,810
We didn't come to stop you.

502
00:51:00,561 --> 00:51:04,730
We figured that your only chance at a
normal life was to leave this world.

503
00:51:04,731 --> 00:51:06,692
[Jasons] Yeah.
He's right. Uh-huh.

504
00:51:07,276 --> 00:51:08,777
We came to say goodbye.

505
00:51:52,112 --> 00:51:53,322
I'm sorry.

506
00:51:54,031 --> 00:51:58,534
I just want you and
Charlie to be safe.

507
00:51:58,535 --> 00:51:59,870
[Jasons] Yeah.

508
00:52:00,704 --> 00:52:01,747
And you...

509
00:52:04,416 --> 00:52:05,625
take care of them.

510
00:52:05,626 --> 00:52:06,793
[Jasons] Yeah.

511
00:52:29,858 --> 00:52:34,445
No, no! No! Why... Why
should he get them?

512
00:52:34,446 --> 00:52:35,656
It's not about him.

513
00:52:36,490 --> 00:52:38,242
It's about what she wants,

514
00:52:39,076 --> 00:52:40,827
and what's best for our son.

515
00:52:41,411 --> 00:52:42,538
[sighs, sniffs]

516
00:52:44,873 --> 00:52:46,250
Let 'em through.

517
00:52:48,669 --> 00:52:49,670
No.

518
00:52:52,422 --> 00:52:53,632
Let 'em through!

519
00:53:03,308 --> 00:53:04,393
Move!

520
00:53:05,811 --> 00:53:07,229
Let 'em through!

521
00:53:13,193 --> 00:53:14,862
[Jasons murmuring]

522
00:53:39,720 --> 00:53:41,430
[Jasons] Charlie. Charlie.

523
00:53:44,141 --> 00:53:45,142
[sniffing]

524
00:53:46,852 --> 00:53:48,145
Daniela.

525
00:54:20,594 --> 00:54:22,596
[Daniela breathing heavily]

526
00:54:28,936 --> 00:54:30,938
["Roost" playing]

527
00:56:38,106 --> 00:56:40,400
[song continues]

528
00:57:06,260 --> 00:57:07,553
